---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Define Success to Achieve It · uxward">
  <style>
    .read-bar { position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; height: 2px; width: 0%; background: var(--signature); z-index: 200; transition: width 80ms linear; }
    .reading-column { max-width: 660px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 var(--gutter-x); }
    .essay-top { padding: var(--space-8) 0 var(--space-7); }
    .essay-top .row { display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between; gap: var(--space-7); flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .essay-top a.back, .essay-top .meta { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--tertiary); text-decoration: none; }
    .essay-top a.back:hover { color: var(--ink); }
    .essay-top .meta .sep { padding: 0 12px; color: var(--rule); }
    .essay-title-block { padding: var(--space-9) 0 var(--space-10); }
    .essay-title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-weight: 300; font-size: clamp(42px, 5.6vw, 76px); line-height: 1.02; letter-spacing: -0.025em; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 30; color: var(--ink); margin: 0; max-width: 820px; }
    .essay-title em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 100, 'WONK' 1; }
    .essay-deck { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-style: italic; font-weight: 300; font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.45; color: var(--body); margin: var(--space-7) 0 0; max-width: 660px; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 36, 'SOFT' 80, 'WONK' 1; }
    .essay-byline { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--tertiary); margin-top: var(--space-8); }
    .essay-body { padding: var(--space-9) 0 var(--space-10); }
    .essay-body p { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-weight: 400; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--body); max-width: 660px; margin: 0 0 var(--space-6); font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 14; text-wrap: pretty; }
    .essay-body p strong { font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink); }
    .essay-body p em { font-style: italic; }
    .essay-body p:first-of-type::first-letter { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-weight: 300; font-size: 5.2em; line-height: 0.88; float: left; padding: 6px 12px 0 0; color: var(--ink); font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 144, 'SOFT' 30, 'WONK' 1; }
    .essay-body h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-weight: 400; font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.18; letter-spacing: -0.015em; color: var(--ink); margin: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-7); font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 96, 'SOFT' 50; max-width: 660px; }
    .essay-body blockquote { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-style: italic; font-weight: 300; font-size: 26px; line-height: 1.35; color: var(--ink); border-left: 3px solid var(--signature); padding: 4px 0 4px var(--space-7); margin: var(--space-9) 0; max-width: 600px; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 96, 'SOFT' 100, 'WONK' 1; }
    .essay-body ol, .essay-body ul { margin: 0 0 var(--space-6); padding-left: var(--space-7); }
    .essay-body ol li, .essay-body ul li { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--body); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 14; }
    .essay-body figure { margin: var(--space-9) 0; }
    .essay-body figure img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }
    .essay-body figure figcaption { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--tertiary); margin-top: var(--space-4); }
    .essay-end { margin-top: var(--space-9); padding-top: var(--space-7); border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
    .essay-end .author { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--tertiary); margin-top: var(--space-6); }
    .more { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); padding: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-9); }
    .more .more-eyebrow { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--tertiary); margin-bottom: var(--space-8); }
    .more-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: var(--space-9); }
    .more-grid .essay-card { text-decoration: none; color: inherit; display: block; }
    .more-grid .essay-card .meta { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--tertiary); margin-bottom: var(--space-5); }
    .more-grid .essay-card .title { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-weight: 400; font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.22; letter-spacing: -0.015em; color: var(--ink); font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 48, 'SOFT' 50; margin: 0 0 var(--space-3); }
    .more-grid .essay-card .deck { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-style: italic; font-size: 16.5px; line-height: 1.5; color: var(--body); margin: 0; font-variation-settings: 'opsz' 24, 'SOFT' 80, 'WONK' 1; }
    .more-grid .essay-card:hover .title { color: var(--tertiary); }
    .all-link { margin-top: var(--space-9); }
    .all-link a { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 18px; color: var(--ink); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 4px; text-decoration-thickness: 1px; }
    @media (max-width: 720px) { .more-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--space-8); } }
  </style>

  <div class="read-bar" id="read-bar" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <div class="reading-column essay-top">
    <div class="row">
      <a class="back" href="/writing">— Back to writing</a>
      <div class="meta">
        <span>Q2 2021</span>
        <span class="sep">·</span>
        <span>Essay</span>
        <span class="sep">·</span>
        <span>9 min read</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="reading-column essay-title-block">
    <h1 class="essay-title">
      <em>Define Success</em> to Achieve It
    </h1>
    <p class="essay-deck">
      The contract said "audit log." That was it. What happened next was predictable. Failing to plan is planning to fail — and this is the story of both.
    </p>
    <div class="essay-byline">— By Brandon E. B. Ward —</div>
  </div>

  <article class="reading-column essay-body">

    <figure>
      <img src="/images/writing/great-wall.jpg" alt="Great Wall of China — Photo by Hanson Lu on Unsplash" />
      <figcaption>Photo by Hanson Lu on Unsplash</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p>
      The contract said the product required an "Audit log." That was it. The web app for a major hospital chain with 35,000 users wanted an audit log, and we were under contractual obligation to deliver one. Whatever "audit log" meant.
    </p>

    <p>
      When I say audit log, what jumps to mind? A log of CRUD activities for key parts of the system? Every change event system-wide? What data does it capture? Who has access? Is there a UI? Is it searchable? What is it actually <em>for</em> — security, compliance, paranoia? When someone views it, what are they looking for?
    </p>

    <figure>
      <img src="/images/writing/dashboard.jpg" alt="Dashboard with data — Photo by Stephen Dawson on Unsplash" />
      <figcaption>Photo by Stephen Dawson on Unsplash</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>The budget was gone, time was up, and everyone was frustrated</h2>

    <p>
      This was only one of hundreds of features called out in bulleted lists in the contract without any real definitions or criteria. Because nothing was clearly defined, every single task required several hours of meetings between clients, project managers, scrum masters, designers, and developers. Everyone had their own interpretation. Even fully-built "done" features were constantly tossed, rewritten, broken, and updated.
    </p>

    <p>
      The project took more than double the original budget and 9 months longer than planned. Even when it shipped, it lacked significant functionality the client had hoped for. Everyone was sad, tired, and spent.
    </p>

    <h2>This is a story about setting yourself up for success</h2>

    <figure>
      <img src="/images/writing/planning.jpg" alt="Planning — Photo by Science in HD on Unsplash" />
      <figcaption>Photo by Science in HD on Unsplash</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p>
      The recipe for success is actually pretty straightforward:
    </p>

    <blockquote>
      Define success. Set clear, articulated goals. Don't underestimate level of effort. Under-promise, over-deliver.
    </blockquote>

    <p>
      <strong>What is the definition of success?</strong> This is the first — and often middle, and last — question I ask when proposing, planning, or kicking off a new project. When we can clearly define what success means to each of us, we can set up a project that will drive us toward that definition. If you don't have a success definition, it's constantly up for debate and redefinition. When everyone has a slightly different opinion as to what success looks like, no amount of expert execution will make everyone happy.
    </p>

    <h2>Clear, articulated goals pave the path to success</h2>

    <figure>
      <img src="/images/writing/paved-path.jpg" alt="Paved path — Photo by Courtney Smith on Unsplash" />
      <figcaption>Photo by Courtney Smith on Unsplash</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p>
      Goals break down "success" into measurable pieces. For designers, our job is to uncover and place the landmarks and signposts that guide teams behind us on the trails we blaze. Skip any of these steps and it's like telling someone to bring you a rock. They bring you a rock. You say that's not the rock you meant. Ad infinitum.
    </p>

    <h2>Slow is smooth, and smooth is fast</h2>

    <figure>
      <img src="/images/writing/sharpen-axe.jpg" alt="Sharpening an axe — Photo by C D-X on Unsplash" />
      <figcaption>Photo by C D-X on Unsplash</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p>
      Moving fast and breaking things may be fun at first, but it's costly. <strong>Stop. Think. Articulate. Define. Refine. Plan.</strong> Do these things and your execution will be faster — and better, with fewer iterations necessary. Spend time sharpening your axe so you swing it less and with less effort.
    </p>

    <figure>
      <img src="/images/writing/measure.jpg" alt="Measuring — Photo by Fleur on Unsplash" />
      <figcaption>Photo by Fleur on Unsplash</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p>
      And constantly measure what matters. <strong>Don't cling to a mistake just because you spent a lot of time and money making it.</strong>
    </p>

    <h2>What we should have done</h2>

    <figure>
      <img src="/images/writing/firefighter.jpg" alt="Firefighter — Photo by LOGAN WEAVER on Unsplash" />
      <figcaption>Photo by LOGAN WEAVER on Unsplash</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <p>
      Looking back, even mid-fire we should have slowed down instead of running faster. If we could go back:
    </p>

    <ol>
      <li><p>Pause all development</p></li>
      <li><p>Define the actual scope of the engagement and append it to the contract</p></li>
      <li><p>Write out every epic, feature, story, and task with acceptance criteria</p></li>
      <li><p>Require interactive prototypes, not annotated PDFs</p></li>
      <li><p>Update budgets and timelines against the new scope</p></li>
    </ol>

    <p>
      We would have delivered faster, more reliably, and for less money.
    </p>

    <p>
      Now, as you go back to your projects or begin the next one: don't plan to fail by failing to plan.
    </p>

    <div class="essay-end">
      <div class="author">— Brandon E. B. Ward · Dallas, TX —</div>
    </div>

  </article>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="more">
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="marker">§ ↗</div>
        <div>
          <div class="more-eyebrow">— More from the writing —</div>
          <div class="more-grid">
            <a class="essay-card" href="/writing">
              <div class="meta">— Essay —</div>
              <h3 class="title">More writing</h3>
              <p class="deck">Thoughts on design, leadership, and the work of making things for people.</p>
            </a>
            <a class="essay-card" href="/writing">
              <div class="meta">— Essay —</div>
              <h3 class="title">More writing</h3>
              <p class="deck">Thoughts on design, leadership, and the work of making things for people.</p>
            </a>
            <a class="essay-card" href="/writing">
              <div class="meta">— Essay —</div>
              <h3 class="title">More writing</h3>
              <p class="deck">Thoughts on design, leadership, and the work of making things for people.</p>
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="all-link">
            <a href="/writing">— All writing →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script>
    (function () {
      var bar = document.getElementById('read-bar');
      if (!bar) return;
      function update() {
        var doc = document.documentElement;
        var max = (doc.scrollHeight - doc.clientHeight);
        var pct = max > 0 ? Math.min(100, Math.max(0, (doc.scrollTop || window.scrollY) / max * 100)) : 0;
        bar.style.width = pct + '%';
      }
      update();
      window.addEventListener('scroll', update, { passive: true });
      window.addEventListener('resize', update);
    })();
  </script>
</Base>
